7:
Doormats like you are always gonna
lose, so why don't you save us the
time and just give up already?
9:
You're really gonna betray us after
all the sucking up you did to Tohru?!
12:
Oh? Were you jealous I paid
attention to him and not you?
18:
Damn it... You'll get what's coming to
you! Just you wait!
24:
Fiiiine. Ugh, are there no child labor
laws here?
33: And that's that. Too easy, ahahaha!
37:
Wow... I'd heard about your abilities
before, but seeing it in person is
impressive! It seems pretty
convenient!
39:
I guess so. I'm pretty strong, but the
whole thing exhausts me. I'd rather
not use it unless I have to.
43:
Hikawa's actually putting some work
in, huh?
47: Yeah, she's been doing a good job.
49:
She always has a lot to say too,
even if it's not always the nicest
things.
53:
Maybe that whole "punch the heck
out of each other" thing actually
knocked some sense into her.
56: Um... Th-thank you for saving us!
59:
Just doing what we can. I know
things are rough right now, but
they'll—
63:
Why are you going after us, huh?!
What'd we ever do to you?
66:
...You use your powers to hurt others.
What did you think would happen?
68:
It's not like we're the only ones! How
come Hikawa gets a pass? It's not
like she's innocent either!
75:
Or did you not know? She used to be
part of Aegis, and she was one of
the worst of us! Did whatever the
hell she wanted to!
78:
Ha, and? Unlike you trash, I actually
had stuff going for me.
82: She's not any different from you.
85:
If you decided to change your ways
and use your powers for good—
88:
Are you kidding me? You had
someone from Aegis here this whole
time?
90:
She should be locked up! It's not
safe to let her walk around freely!
93:
That is NOT how things work around
here—
97:
There are plenty of people with
powers outside of Aegis, you know.
Both in Shibuya and Palpebra.
100:
Yeah, but these Aegis kids have
attacked people before! They're
rotten to the core!
101:
How do you know she's really
changed her ways?!
107:
...Haha! Nobodies like you get scared
so easily! Must be soooo tough,
living without any powers to back
you up.
109:
Sorry for being better than you!
Gosh, this is just too funny.
Ahahahahaha!
117: ...Hmph. What a pain in the ass.
121:
I'm gonna take my break now. It's
the least I get after doing all the
work, right?
127:
...Guess it's no surprise they see it
that way.
130:
...Eh, whatever! I can always find a
new gang to run with when it comes
down to it. Not like I'm attached to
anybody here.
134: There you are. I was looking for you.
138:
Ugh, of course it's you. After I finally
cheered myself up too.
145: Yeah, no. What would be the point?
153:
Who knows? Maybe those guys over
there can take me somewhere fun.
156:
Why? I know that's not what you
really want to do.
160:
You... Why don't you mind your own
business?!
163:
I get it. You can't be disappointed if
you throw your expectations away
first, right? That's why you always
pretend not to care.
177:
What's your problem anyway? No
sane person would be bugging me
this much.
179:
Ahahaha! Wait, don't tell me. You're
one of THOSE people, and you've
fallen for ME?
183:
I did start liking you, but probably
not in the way you're thinking right
now.
190:
The lies you tell yourself remind me
of my own.
192:
I know that doesn't make us exactly
the same...
199:
But... if you want a reason, then it's
because I enjoy talking with you.
208:
You can relax. I'm not gonna do
anything stupid. I'll get back on my
own later.
